          {
            "type": "html",
            "text": " arbitrary-length collections (sets, vectors, matrices) receive a surrogate identifier and a separate schema where they are broken down into constituent parts. For example, a set of (integer|string) in myTable might be broken down into TABLE myTable(mySetID,attr1,attr2) and TABLE setDescriptors(setID,anInteger,aString). A vector or matrix might also receive a positional argument or two, e.g.  vectorDescriptor(vectorID,nPos,anInteger). ",
