            "type": "html",
            "text": "\nTools would be able to provide arbitrary higher operators, such as pattern-matching, definitions for joins, functions, etc. Tools would provide the <i>extrinsic</i> semantics for values - e.g. interpreting a given record as a command or query or identifier or physical address or statement of truth. Not all tools (e.g. transport and storage) are interested in such extrinsic semantics, and only need to concern themselves with intrinsic semantics. If standards are to be placed on these <i>extrinsic</i> semantics, that can be performed with <i>a different</i> set of standards, likely standardized specific to the domain (e.g. physics) or the class of tools (e.g. DBMSs). ",
